text.section:
In this section, "fire and explosive investigator" means an individual who:
is assigned full time to the fire and explosive investigations section of the City of Hagerstown Fire Marshal's Office and is a paid employee;
has been employed by the City of Hagerstown Fire Department as a firefighter for at least 5 years;
has successfully completed a training program from a police training school approved by the Police Training Commission established under Title 3, Subtitle 2 of the Public Safety Article; and
at all times maintains active certification by the Police Training Commission.

Except as provided in subsection (c) of this section, a fire and explosive investigator has the same authority granted to the State Fire Marshal or a full-time investigative and inspection assistant of the Office of the State Fire Marshal under § 2-208 of this subtitle:
while operating in the City of Hagerstown; and
while operating outside the City of Hagerstown when:
the fire and explosive investigator is participating in a joint investigation with officials from another state, federal, or local law enforcement unit, at least one of which has local jurisdiction;
the fire and explosive investigator is rendering assistance to another law enforcement officer;
the fire and explosive investigator is acting at the request of a law enforcement officer or State law enforcement officer; or
an emergency exists.
